***What is the maximum lease payment that would be acceptable to the company?***

As said before, the maximum lease payment that would be acceptable to the company is the value that makes the $\operatorname{NPV}$ and $\operatorname{NAL}$, zero. Then, if we have from the previous section that: 
$$
\begin{align*}
\operatorname{VPN}&= \$7,300,000 – \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^5}}{0.0632}\\[10pt] 
0 &= \$7,300,000 – \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^5}}{0.0632}
\end{align*}
$$
Then, 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Annual cash flow}&= \frac{\$7,300,000}{\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^5}}{0.0632}}\\[30pt]
&=\frac{ \$7,300,000 }{4.1759}\\[10pt]
&=\$ 1,748,107.09
\end{align*}
$$
